  "instructions": [
    "Preheat oven to 375°F (190°C).",
    "Wrap the comal in aluminum foil and place it on a baking sheet.",
    "Drizzle the olive oil on the comal and sprinkle with salt and black pepper.",
    "Cook the farfalle pasta according to the package instructions and set aside.",
    "In a saucepan, heat the coconut milk over medium heat, then add the chopped onion and minced garlic, cook until softened, stirring occasionally.",
    "Add the ground turkey to the saucepan and cook until browned, breaking it up into small pieces as it cooks.",
    "Add the chopped scotch bonnet peppers, canned diced tomatoes, and baking powder to the saucepan and stir to combine.",
    "Pour the saucepan mixture over the cooked farfalle pasta and stir to combine.",
    "Transfer the pasta mixture to the prepared comal and smooth the top with a spatula.",
    "Sprinkle the shredded cheddar cheese and crushed corn tortilla chips on top of the pasta mixture, if using.",
    "Bake for 20-25 minutes or until the top is golden brown and the cheese is melted.",
    "Remove from the oven and let cool for a few minutes before serving, garnished with chopped fresh cilantro, if desired."
  ],
